The paper focuses on resilient routing and fast failover mechanisms in Software-Defined Networks (SDN), which are primarily studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also analyzes the correctness and load-balancing metrics, which are relevant to the systems and information theory (cs.SI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents algorithms and simulations, which are relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
